page.title: 02General Review 2
page.content:
There is the{parish church}and churchyard of Lytchett Matravers. Two{main roads}traverse the area. The A350 from south east towards north west and the A31 east to west with a {junction}with the A350 at Round House Roundabout. It is a{peaceful, quiet and {beautiful}tract of farmland.
This area was surveyed by{Shirley {Percival}and{Rosemary Endecott, members of the{Womens' Institute}and the{Lytchett Matravers Natural {Amenities Group (N.A.G.).}They were assisted by Philip Endecott, age 15, who advised on the use of the computer.
